article.description: Brandon Sherrod made all seven of his field goal attempts and scored 19 points, leading Yale to an 81-58 win over Penn on Friday night.
article.headline: Sherrod scores 19 to help Yale roll past Penn 81-58
article.linkText: Sherrod scores 19 to help Yale roll past Penn 81-58
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Brandon Sherrod made all seven of his field goal attempts and scored 19 points, leading Yale to an 81-58 win over Penn on Friday night. Justin Sears added 16 points and Makai Mason 14 for the Bulldogs (12-5, 3-0 Ivy), who won their seventh straight. Yale shot better from the field (30 for 50) than it did from the foul line (17 of 33). Nick Victor had nine rebounds to go with six points as the Bulldogs had a 41-25 rebounding advantage. Matt Howard made 7 of 10 shots and led Penn (6-10, 0-2) with 17 points but the Quakers shot 40 percent (20 of 50) and were just 13 of 23 from the line. Yale scored the first eight points but never got the lead past 10. Sears' layup made it 41-31 at the half. The Bulldogs steadily pulled way in the second half.
